did.abstract: This collection documents the construction and remodeling to the buildings and grounds of Central Washington University. Ellensburg, WA, 1954-2000.

bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: Central Washington University's Facilities Management Department was initially established under the supervision of the Washington State Normal School Board of Trustees when the school opened in 1891. In 1910, a Supervisor of Buildings and Grounds was appointed and given the responsibility for facilities management of the campus. During the 1920s, a Business Manager replaced the Supervisor of Buildings and Grounds consolidating departments. The Facilities Management Department was reorganized in 1986 and included the planning division.

scopecontent.p: This collection represents growth at Central Washington University, 1954-2000. The included Campus Site and Development Committee minutes and correspondence outline the planning of Central's Facilities Management Department. This collection also includes photographs and drawings that document additions and modifications to buildings and landscaping on campus.

odd.p: Central Washington University began as the Washington State Normal School in 1891. In 1937, the school was rechristened the Central Washington College of Education. In 1961, the school became Central Washington State College and, finally, in 1977, Central Washington University.

arrangement.p: Organized into four series: I. Campus Site and Development Committee; II. Technical Data Collection; III. Photographs; IV. Oversized materials

accessrestrict.p: Open to the public for educational research.

scopecontent.p: This series contains planning documents of the Campus Site and Development Committee. The files of the committee's meeting minutes also include as attachments documents which were discussed at the meetings. These include planning documents for buildings, facilities, grounds, and any changes to the campus. Another group of files are the correspondence files for the committee. These files include letters concerning membership to the committee as well as letters concerning the campus facilities.

scopecontent.p: This series contains the technical files of the facilities department. Included are planning documents, drawings and reports. This includes planning documents for new buildings and the remodeling of old buildings. Also included are energy audits and other technical reports. Also present are files of the utilities on campus. These files are arranged by the Technical Data (TD) Collection number which was assigned by the facilities department.

arrangement.p: These files are arranged by the Technical Data (TD) Collection number, which was assigned by the Facilities Management Department.

scopecontent.p: This series primarily contains slides, though some negatives and contact sheets are also present. The slides are undated, though they appear to be from the late 1970s and 1980s. Pictured is the conference center--the building and activities in the building. Also included are slides depicting food services, including banquets and events.

arrangement.p: Arranged topically and in original order.
